# Dive Core Interfaces and Packages

## Core Packages

### Main Package (`github.com/getstingrai/dive`)
The main package defines the core interfaces and types used throughout Dive:

- `Workflow` - Template for repeatable processes
- `Task` - Unit of work that can be executed
- `Agent` - AI agent that performs tasks
- `Environment` - Running instance of a project
- `OutputFormat` - Format for task results (text, markdown, json)
- `TaskStatus` - Status of a task (queued, active, paused, completed, etc.)

### LLM Package (`github.com/getstingrai/dive/llm`)
Handles LLM interactions and tool definitions:

- `LLM` - Interface for LLM providers
- `StreamingLLM` - Interface for streaming LLM responses
- `Tool` - Interface for LLM tools
- `ToolDefinition` - Definition of a tool's parameters and behavior
- `Message` - LLM message structure
- `Response` - LLM response structure

### Document Package (`github.com/getstingrai/dive/document`)
Manages document storage and retrieval:

- `Repository` - Interface for document storage
- `Document` - Interface for document content
- `ListDocumentInput` - Search criteria for documents
- `ListDocumentOutput` - Results of document listing

### Memory Package (`github.com/getstingrai/dive/memory`)
Handles agent memory and context:

- `Memory` - Interface for memory operations
- `VectorStorage` - Interface for vector storage
- `Embedder` - Interface for text embedding
- `Message` - Memory message structure
- `Thread` - Conversation thread structure

### Events Package (`github.com/getstingrai/dive/events`)
Manages event streaming:

- `Event` - Event structure
- `Stream` - Interface for receiving events
- `Publisher` - Interface for sending events
- `Handler` - Interface for handling events

### Workflow Package (`github.com/getstingrai/dive/workflow`)
Implements workflow execution:

- `Workflow` - Workflow implementation
- `Execution` - Single workflow run
- `Runner` - Manages workflow executions
- `Store` - Interface for execution persistence
- `MetricsCollector` - Interface for execution metrics

### Graph Package (`github.com/getstingrai/dive/graph`)
Handles task dependency management:

- `Node` - Interface for graph nodes
- `Graph` - Graph implementation for task ordering

### Retry Package (`github.com/getstingrai/dive/retry`)
Handles error recovery:

- `RecoverableError` - Interface for recoverable errors

## Key Interfaces

### Agent Interfaces
```go
type Agent interface {
    Name() string
    Description() string
    Instructions() string
    IsSupervisor() bool
    Subordinates() []string
    Work(ctx context.Context, task Task) (events.Stream, error)
}

type RunnableAgent interface {
    Agent
    Start(ctx context.Context) error
    Stop(ctx context.Context) error
    IsRunning() bool
}

type EventHandlerAgent interface {
    Agent
    AcceptedEvents() []string
    HandleEvent(ctx context.Context, event *events.Event) error
}
```

### Workflow Interface
```go
type Workflow interface {
    Name() string
    Description() string
    Tasks() []Task
    Inputs() map[string]WorkflowInput
    Outputs() map[string]WorkflowOutput
    Validate() error
}
```

### Task Interface
```go
type Task interface {
    Name() string
    Description() string
    ExpectedOutput() string
    Dependencies() []string
    AssignedAgent() Agent
    Validate() error
    Prompt(opts TaskPromptOptions) string
}
```

### Environment Interface
```go
type Environment interface {
    Name() string
    Description() string
    Repository() document.Repository
    Agents() []Agent
    GetAgent(name string) (Agent, error)
    RegisterAgent(agent Agent) error
    Workflows() []Workflow
    GetWorkflow(id string) (Workflow, error)
    StartWorkflow(ctx context.Context, workflow Workflow) error
    StopWorkflow(ctx context.Context, id string) error
}
```

### Tool Interface
```go
type Tool interface {
    Definition() *ToolDefinition
    Call(ctx context.Context, input string) (string, error)
    ShouldReturnResult() bool
}
```

## Configuration

Dive supports configuration through multiple formats:
- JSON
- YAML
- HCL (HashiCorp Configuration Language)

Configuration is handled by the `teamconf` package which provides:
- `TeamDefinition` - Serializable representation of a team
- `AgentConfig` - Agent configuration
- `Task` - Task configuration
- `Document` - Document configuration
- `ToolConfig` - Tool configuration


